                "href": "/profile/Joshua-Stone-104"
            },
            "answer_text": "Not generally. If it\u2019s a scholarly book, like a biography or a history book, the author is staking their professional reputation on the veracity of the contents. Those will have a list of references and citations in the back, but it is the readers\u2019 responsibility to confirm the claims, and if the author presents their citations in proper context. If it\u2019s a novel or a political book, or a self help book, it could be full of lies and you might never know. ",
